{"abstract": "Machine learning for sign languages is bottlenecked by data. In this paper, we present YouTube-ASL, a large-scale, open-domain corpus of American Sign Language (ASL) videos and accompanying English captions drawn from YouTube. With ~1000 hours of videos and>2500 unique signers, YouTube-ASL is ~3x as large and has ~10x as many unique signers as the largest prior ASL dataset. We train baseline models for ASL to English translation on YouTube-ASL and evaluate them on How2Sign, where we achieve a new finetuned state of the art of 12.39 BLEU and, for the first time, report zero-shot results.", "referenced_work_ids": ["108c9f268b3a89d2570901b7997b683c8cbbe192", "3bbc8841012fdb5971d1c86dff528edd8590f1b8", "06c8cdd8c517e45adcbb519d77c897aaa6766282", "a02fbaf22237a1aedacb1320b6007cd70c1fe6ec", "458e5d02c0612deae07e5fb241179b52429a81d4", "7c73fe9266db0b35f551645ca37c6e7ce0980c4b", "be54fc78e86fb3e65964fbfb904f22eb9927502f", "7366fe7b4e7756dd13220d29077142ff802b41b3", "2dc5bd35be89eaa336384a3b8cd4b611485c1602", "dfd104dd0ff28b1bde2fbd4c4d6d3ccb4761f639", "789b8487da7188442085983caba3ffaae05531e9", "7811df11a75f58646d04b3132d35f0656e50a109", "c4358134954d8e62939c3a8b9ba8e953d951f73b", "06f18e61b6f8c7b04e512b93388bc2b341327993", "7663a568ce56a0ce232a06d59b927b2e7010ab48", "932168d1c27390506049adf679b42d3aac53f61c", "58cdf6a994558124d5c4f836473837e778530be2", "4ae52766028e69186052ea8f33a137fbbbdb986a", "7153c3b129f1e6423dea6afcdbb57466466cd2cc", "0e141942fa265142f41a2a26eb17b6005d3af29e", "05dcdfece56d1869895f53ed581d8ad64118c05f", "a1e2665ac39dcb389e12f3f993004b4b4651826d", "874063b6c71aef8382eb66a66d8a1c1188e78a9a", "6c4b76232bb72897685d19b3d264c6ee3005bc2b", "0e112053a93beba08a998d71ba7e27620c43a0d4", "c7fd5973a2cb3f7c6a5df0120400bc47b2f2bacf", "1c44a3cde07f3f2ffd8880b441449483ed74fc5f", "9e8db1519245426f3a78752a3d8360484f4626b1", "310a8e2c9f2650fa2e44fdf0d82d11c0cb3e387e", "74669631d3f1fcc06d0e5e5daa7e4bfd5b6f6b59", "c840615f7e079db25bd45b8baf36b3523c2c2474", "b